      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHERE'S THE BOSS (3) has missed the placings at his last couple but was in the money three back when third (17.28) at this track in a Grade 5. Better than last run and makes appeal this time. MAKE A MILE (8) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by a nose at this track in a handy 17.25 beating Lady Blazington. The form out of last race has been strong. One of main contenders. ROBELL THEA (1) drew an outside box and was game in defeat when only 1.3 lengths from the winner Nicky Aces in third(17.59) at this track. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Can measure up. CHAMPAGNE TALKS (2) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
